CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 28, 1939, pg. 1 reads: "Dr. Jack Greenlee Victim Of Fatal Automobile Accident - Interior and exterior of the coupe in which Dr. Jack Greenlee met death when he was struck by a truck on the Ohio River boulevard while driving to Pittsburgh from Sewickley, Tuesday morning. The popular young physician and surgeon died five minutes after he had been admitted to the Suburban General Hospital.  Eyewitnesses to the accident said he never had a chance.  Note the manner in which the side of the automobile is crushed in and the blood spattered on the back of the seat.  Inset: Dr. Greenlee, as an intern at Marcy Hospital.  He was a graduate of Howard University Medical School.  Photos of wreck by Teenie Harris"
TitMainTitle: Interior of wrecked car, driven by Dr. Jack Greenlee, with blood on driver's seat, in front of wall with Oldsmobile logo, another version
